# Prismarine Viewer

[prismarine-viewer](https://www.npmjs.com/package/prismarine-viewer) · Used in this repo by `viewer/bot.js`. For a **full Minecraft client in the browser** (mineflayer + viewer over a WebSocket proxy), see [prismarine-web-client](https://github.com/PrismarineJS/prismarine-web-client) and rule `prismarine-web-client.mdc`.

## Install and use

```bash
npm install prismarine-viewer
```

```js
const { mineflayer: mineflayerViewer } = require('prismarine-viewer');

bot.once('spawn', () => {
  mineflayerViewer(bot, { port: 3007, firstPerson: true });
});
```

- `port` — HTTP server port (e.g. 3000, 3007).
- `firstPerson: true` — bot POV; `false` for bird's-eye.
- Opens a live 3D view in the browser; useful for debugging movement and world state.
